      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm trying to wrap my head around a legal debate. Is it actually possible to maintain a truly secular state if we let religious groups opt-out of government laws that go against their beliefs? Or is that just an inevitable part of protecting religious freedom? Which way do you think is the more stable approach for a modern democracy?",
