    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Wait, \"surrender of state authority\"? That sounds pretty intense. Aren't there cases where forcing someone to violate their core conscience is actually what causes social instability? Like, if the state starts forcing people to act against their most fundamental beliefs, doesn't that just radicalize them and cause more chaos in the long run?",
